column18: Indicates the different participants per experiment
indicates the result of the team in this round (criterion: the team wins if the sum of rolls is greater than 10); 0 = loss, 1 = win
indicates the choice of die for each player (1 = bad/cheap die, 2 = neutral die, 3 = good/expensive die)
indicates what numbers the players rolled with their dice (from 1 (lowest) to 6 (highest) )
Money that each player earned/lost in this round (depends on what die the player chose and whether the team won or lost)
Responsibility rating for each player; participants attributed blame for losses (0 = no blame 10 = high blame) and credit for wins (0 = no credit, 10 = high credit)

column17: Note that in Experiment 1, phase 2 was missing (i.e. there are only 20 rounds per participants in experiment 1 but in experiment 2 there are 34 rounds per participant)
